=head1 NAME

dosspwrite - write messages to Windows PC

=head1 SYNOPSIS

B<dosspwrite>
I<options>

=head1 DESCRIPTION

B<Dosspwrite> sends messages to Windows PCs similar to spwrite(8) does
for user's terminals in response to the equivalents of the C<-w>
and C<-A> options of gspl-pr(1). This is only done for jobs which
originated on Windows PCs.

The Windows PC must be running B<sprserv> for this to be effectual.

If the job was submitted by a user working from a client with a
DHCP-allocated IP address, a message may be received on all clients
currently logged-in with that user name.

=head1 FILES

F<int-config>
message file

=head1 ENVIRONMENT

